 Start ngrok for Jenkins in terminal

If Jenkins is running locally on port 8080, open a new terminal and run:
 ngrok http 8080

This will generate an HTTPS public URL like:
Copy that add it in git hub repo web hook


2. In Jenkins: Enable GitHub webhook trigger
Go to your Jenkins job (Pipeline or Freestyle).

Click Configure.

Scroll to Build Triggers.

✅ Check GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling.

Save.




3. In GitHub: Add webhook
Go to your GitHub repo.

Navigate to Settings → Webhooks → Add webhook.

Fill:

Payload URL:

bash
Copy
Edit
https://abc123.ngrok.io/github-webhook/
Content type: application/json

Events: Choose Just the push event

Click Add webhook.

